## âš™ï¸ Installation

### Backend Setup:

1. ğŸ“¥ Clone the repository:
   ```bash
   git clone https://github.com/your-username/customer-management.git
   cd customer-management/backend
   ```

2. ğŸ› ï¸ Set up the database:
   - Create a ğŸ˜ PostgreSQL database and update the `application.properties` file with your database credentials:
     ```properties
     spring.datasource.url=jdbc:postgresql://localhost:5432/customer_db
     spring.datasource.username=your-username
     spring.datasource.password=your-password
     ```

3. ğŸš€ Run database migrations:
   ```bash
   mvn flyway:migrate
   ```

4. ğŸ› ï¸ Build and run the backend:
   ```bash
   mvn spring-boot:run
   ```

### Frontend Setup:

1. Navigate to the frontend directory:
   ```bash
   cd ../frontend
   ```

2. ğŸ“¥ Install dependencies:
   ```bash
